                        <provenance>
                            <p>Colophon on folio <locus from="153a" to="153a">153a</locus> is
                                signed by <persName role="scribe" key="">Muhammad Amin bin 'Abdallah</persName>.</p>
                            <p>Part of library of <persName type="standard"
                                ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/51695910/#Silvestre_de_Sacy,_A._I._(Antoine_Isaac),_1758-1838"
                                key="person_51695910">Antoine Isaac, Baron Silvestre de Sacy
                                (1758-1838)</persName>, French orientalist, which was sold in
                                three public auctions during the 1840s. The manuscript
                                then became part of the collection of the Persian scholar <persName
                                    type="standard"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/#Bland,_Nathaniel,_1803-1865"
                                    key="person_20108923">Nathaniel Bland (1803-1865)</persName>.
                                Bland’s oriental manuscripts were sold through Bernard Quaritch in
                                1866 to <persName type="standard"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/#Crawford,_Alexander_Crawford_Lindsay,_Earl_of,_1812-1880"
                                    key="person_97751058">Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of
                                    Crawford</persName>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
